<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="7218" type="taxon discussion">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="7218">Taxon discussion</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="7218">
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Mycetophilidae" genus="Boletina" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Boletina pallidula" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="7218" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pallidula">Boletina pallidula</taxonomicName>
was described by Edwards (
<bibRefCitation author="Edwards, F. W." journalOrPublisher="Transactions of the Royal Entomological Society of London" pageId="0" pageNumber="7218" pagination="505 - 670" title="British fungus-gnats (Diptera, Mycetophilidae). With a revised generic classiﬁcation of the family." volume="1925" year="1925">Edwards 1925</bibRefCitation>
) from the British Isles, and the male hypopygium has been later illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Hutson, AM." journalOrPublisher="Handbooks for Identification of British Insects" pageId="0" pageNumber="7218" title="Mycetophilidae (Bolitophilinae, Ditiomyiinae, Diadocidiinae, Keroplatinae, Sciophilinae and Manotinae). Diptera, Nematocera" year="1980">Hutson et al. 1980</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Zaitzev, A. I." journalOrPublisher="Nauka, Moscow" pageId="0" pageNumber="7218" title="Fungus gnats of the fauna of Russia and adjacent regions. Part 1." year="1994">Zaitzev 1994</bibRefCitation>
. The species has a European range, including Fennoscandia, northern Russia, Central Europe, Bulgaria and Hungary (
<bibRefCitation pageId="0" pageNumber="7218">Chandler 2014</bibRefCitation>
). Sasakawa (
<bibRefCitation author="Sasakawa, M." journalOrPublisher="Transactions of the Shikoku Entomological Society" pageId="0" pageNumber="7218" pagination="293 - 306" title="Fungus gnats associated with flowers of the genus Arisaema (Araceae). Part 2. Keroplatidae and Mycetophilidae (Diptera)" volume="20" year="1994">Sasakawa 1994</bibRefCitation>
) described 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Centricae" family="Biddulphiaceae" genus="B." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" lsidName="B. subnitidula" order="Biddulphiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="7218" phylum="Diatomeae" rank="species" species="subnitidula">B. subnitidula</taxonomicName>
from the Chiba prefekture in Japan based on material collected from 
<taxonomicName genus="Arisema" lsidName="Arisema serratum" pageId="0" pageNumber="7218" rank="species" species="serratum">Arisema serratum</taxonomicName>
flowers. Sasakawa's description is very detailed, including illustrations on the male hypopygium, and hence we propose it as a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Centricae" family="Biddulphiaceae" genus="B." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" lsidName="B. pallidula" order="Biddulphiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="7218" phylum="Diatomeae" rank="species" species="pallidula">B. pallidula</taxonomicName>
. In his discussion on 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Centricae" family="Biddulphiaceae" genus="B." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" lsidName="B. subnitidula" order="Biddulphiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="7218" phylum="Diatomeae" rank="species" species="subnitidula">B. subnitidula</taxonomicName>
Sasakawa (
<bibRefCitation author="Sasakawa, M." journalOrPublisher="Transactions of the Shikoku Entomological Society" pageId="0" pageNumber="7218" pagination="293 - 306" title="Fungus gnats associated with flowers of the genus Arisaema (Araceae). Part 2. Keroplatidae and Mycetophilidae (Diptera)" volume="20" year="1994">Sasakawa 1994</bibRefCitation>
, p. 300) does not mention 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Centricae" family="Biddulphiaceae" genus="B." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" lsidName="B. pallidula" order="Biddulphiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="7218" phylum="Diatomeae" rank="species" species="pallidula">B. pallidula</taxonomicName>
; instead, he compares his new species to rather distant species 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Centricae" family="Biddulphiaceae" genus="B." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" lsidName="B. nitida" order="Biddulphiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="7218" phylum="Diatomeae" rank="species" species="nitida">B. nitida</taxonomicName>
Grzegorzek and 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Centricae" family="Biddulphiaceae" genus="B." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" lsidName="B. dispecta" order="Biddulphiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="7218" phylum="Diatomeae" rank="species" species="dispecta">B. dispecta</taxonomicName>
Dziedzicki. It is likely that Sasakawa was not aware of 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Centricae" family="Biddulphiaceae" genus="B." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" lsidName="B. pallidula" order="Biddulphiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="7218" phylum="Diatomeae" rank="species" species="pallidula">B. pallidula</taxonomicName>
while describing 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Centricae" family="Biddulphiaceae" genus="B." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" lsidName="B. subnitidula" order="Biddulphiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="7218" phylum="Diatomeae" rank="species" species="subnitidula">B. subnitidula</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
